<note><title>Intro</title><content><![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd">

<en-note><div><div><span style="font-style: italic;">Throughout the video, have background footage of parts of later (&quot;more advanced&quot;) episodes (i.e. you can only publish this vid once you have a couple others at least in the backlog.)</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Welcome to <span style="font-style: italic;">From 0 to Mod</span> [from naught to mod], a video tutorial series in which we tackle all the key concepts you will need to create mods for Avorion. We&apos;ll start at the very beginning, assuming you have zero coding knowledge, and work our way up from there to introduce you to all the tidbits and nuances that the Avorion environment has to offer.</div><div><br/></div><div>Through this series, I hope to show you that modding Avorion is not only easy, but extremely fulfilling, and that there&apos;s some <span style="font-style: italic;">pretty crazy</span> things you can accomplish with some surprisingly simple tricks and hacks.</div><div><br/></div><div>I&apos;ll attempt to teach you not only the way to create a specific type of mod, but a more fundamental paradigm that will help you think of ways in which you can teach yourself how to create other types of mods that we might not cover here in the series, and how you can help yourself find all the things you need to get started on that journey.</div><div><br/></div><div>Specifically, the range of topics we will cover varies from:</div><ul><li><div>installing and launching a code editor for the first time;</div></li><li><div>finding the inspiration for your mod in examples and base game code;</div></li><li><div>creating the scaffolds for your mod;</div></li><li><div>diving into the specifics through use of the docs and the base game codebase;</div></li><li><div>creating code libraries for later use in all your other mods;</div></li><li><div>and some specific examples, including:</div></li><ul><li><div>making your own custom <b>Faction Pack</b> for custom <b>Factions</b>;</div></li><li><div>a new <span style="font-weight: bold;">Command</span> that provides some basic functionality;</div></li><li><div>a new <span style="font-weight: bold;">System Module Upgrade</span>;</div></li><li><div>a new <span style="font-weight: bold;">Event</span>&nbsp;that introduces waves of enemies to fight;</div></li><li><div>a new <span style="font-weight: bold;">Mission</span>;</div></li><li><div>a new <span style="font-weight: bold;">Item</span>&nbsp;to be sold at <span style="font-weight: bold;">Equipment Merchants</span>;</div></li><li><div>a new <span style="font-weight: bold;">Turret</span>;</div></li><li><div>a new <span style="font-weight: bold;">Sector</span> to be generated in the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Galaxy</span>;</div></li><li><div>custom <span style="font-weight: bold;">Soundtrack</span> using the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Music Manager</span>;</div></li><li><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Entity</span> scripts to create a custom <span style="font-weight: bold;">Merchant</span>;</div></li><li><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">AI</span> scripts for custom <span style="font-weight: bold;">Captained Ship</span> behaviour;</div></li><li><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Story</span> scripts for custom storylines;</div></li><li><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Entity</span> scripts to introduce completely custom behaviour to every <span style="font-weight: bold;">Ship</span> in the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Galaxy</span>;</div></li><li><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">custom</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">UI</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">elements</span> for your scripts;</div></li><li><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Player</span> scripts to modify behaviour for all <span style="font-weight: bold;">Players</span>&nbsp;in your <span style="font-weight: bold;">Galaxy</span>;</div></li><li><div>custom <b>Ship Generator</b>&nbsp;assets.</div></li></ul><li><div>a look through more advanced mods that introduce completely novel mechanics into the game, and how to learn from their example.</div></li></ul><div><br/></div><div>So... I hope to see you soon in our first installment of...&nbsp;<span style="font-style: italic;">From 0 to Mod</span>!</div><div><br/></div></div><div><br/></div></en-note>]]></content><created>20200212T163009Z</created><updated>20200213T180608Z</updated><note-attributes><author>Shrooblord</author><source>desktop.win</source><source-application>evernote.win32</source-application></note-attributes></note></en-export>
